channel.title: Errors, scripters heres somethin u can help me wit
channel.description:
Ok i ran windows 2000 update a couple weeks ago without an active internet connection (like a dumb) and went to control pannel, which said:
an error has occured in the script on this page.
line: 33 char:17 error: error loading dll code: 0 url: file://C:\WINNT\Web\controlp.htt
and the right side of the control pannel doesnt show any descriptions for anything i select.
den i go to add/remove programs i get this:
an error has occured in the script on this page
line: 21 char:1 error: object doesnt support this property or method code: 0 url: res://sp3res.dll/default.hta
and none of my programs show up..
den i go to c:\program files\
an error has occured in the script on this page.
line: 361 char: 13 error: 'gFolder.HaveToShowWebViewBarracade' is null or not a object code: 0 url: file://C:\Program Files\Folder.htt
and NO FOLDERS SHOW UP!!!! only wen i use task manager all folders show up...
i download a game, called eviflames mmorpg, its a mu online private server i love, with the title muset.dat or some crap similar... and it says:
cannot load library/dll
the folder ones are what i think are caused by internet explorer problems, and i tried reinstalling IE but it doesnt do a thing.
and zomfg.... the stupid media player 9 doesnt work AT ALL anymore... i cant even reinstall that either... install shield is fuked... and i believe i had a kernel32.dll error also, idk...
[size=50pt] HELP MEH!!!! [/size]
EDIT: also i noticed when i run AN installation program i get an error like so:
C:\WINNT\SYSTEM32\msvbvm60.dll
Unable to register the DLL/OCX: DllRegisterServer failed; code 0x80029c4A.
click retry to try again, ignore to proceed anyway (not recommended), or abort to cancel installation
